        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">I'm Roman Waters, a web designer &amp; developer. I live in Brighton, UK</h1>
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-7 text-base">
          <p>I've been bringing things to life on the internet for a long time,
             putting together my first website at 10 years old, on a pleasant Friday afternoon.
              I'm very lucky to have been encouraged to be inquisitive;
               and to be able to start building a valuable life skill from such a young age.</p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-8 mb-4">My Approach to Web Development</h2>
          <p>I apply a holistic approach to web development, whether crafting a custom-coded solution
             or building a comprehensive WordPress ecommerce store. Working collaboratively from the ground up,
              I design SEO-ready systems that perform beautifully and convert visitors into customers.
               Most importantly, I ensure you're empowered with the knowledge and
               tools to make the most of your digital investment.</p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mt-8 mb-4">Life Beyond Development</h2>
          <p>Of course, there's more to life than the digital world. A surprising one is my work with young people
            as life coach! Working with a local charity to empower young people has earned me
        <a class="font-bold underline animate-pulse-slow" target=”_blank” href="https://www.rockinghorse.org.uk/news/rockinghorse-funded-service-wins-national-award/">recognition</a> and
      fulfilment, as well as honing my skills in problem-solving and adaptability.</p>
          <p>Along the way, I picked up a degree in business and media. Valuable for any freelancer, and makes for a especially potent combination when
             combined with natural analytical and asset based approach.</p>
